metadata.name: Distant Views #118
metadata.description:
This work explores generative way of painting landscapes on canvas. Algorithm uses backward moves with big polygon brush to produce mountain-like structures. Shades of randomly selected color make illusion of distance and adds to diversity of terrain. Sun and Moon can have different positions on the horizon or not be visible at all. Their color changes depending on the position. Besides night and day, there are three rough variants of composition based on percentage that sky takes on canvas. There is a also chance to have snowy mountain on top.

Artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

December, 2021.

metadata.name: Chaotic Attraction #10
metadata.description:
The world shifts into chaos, which we then attempt to correct. Chaos is the world's natural state. Similar to how a strong emote slowly defends itself until a new one "corrects" its direction. Simply put, this is entropy as defined by thermodynamics.
Order is free will; chaos is fate. We are all drawn to fate in some way, that instinctive desire to watch a fire burn. Every single one of us is just as wired for order as for chaos.
Maintaining order requires work, sacrifice, and effort. The beauty of letting go of inhibitions and returning to our more primal fascination is intoxicating in chaos where we only need to exist.

And that almost acts as our adrenaline, reflecting on everyone. A chaotic environment might energize them, release all those feel-good brain chemicals, and actually make them feel good.
Another thing to consider is that most creative work is chaotic and random, and most artists intentionally introduce chaos or randomness into their work in order to find fresh "opportunities" and rekindle their creativity. You must constantly use new colors if you want to keep the world colorful. A world of white and black can be creative; a world of blue and red cannot. Using the same colors repeatedly in a "imitative" manner will only kill it.
Chaos gives life more color, possibilities, chances, and opportunities, and it's full of pleasant and unpleasant surprises. People have become so dumb and lazy that they are no longer able to make the best of both bad and positive circumstances and events.

Wait a moment it takes a while to be rendered
---
Created using vanilla javascript
KrouniHatim - Nov22
---
(CC BY-ND 4.0)

metadata.name: 0RAL B1NARY: “BINARY ODE” #275
metadata.description:
An “algorhythmic” exploration of the oral/aural tradition in poetry. 

“Zero is a time of night.
Zero is the color of snow.
Zero is the space between notes.
Zero is the silence between words.
Zero is the pause before breath.
Zero is void in the heart of a crowd.
Zero is not nothing, but it’s not everything.
One is a time of day.
One is the color of spring grass in sunlight.
One is the warmth at the back of my neck when I turn to find you standing there.
One is the rhythm at the base of my spine.
One is the peace at the core of my being.
One is the sound of your voice in the dark.
And one more thing:
Without one I am nothing…”
–Technelegy 
 

Fusing AI-powered verse, spoken word, original music and visuals all in generative composition, this playful ode to our universal language is inspired by Stiles’ binary-based art and Stern’s performative poetics. The experiment centers on a transhuman poem by Stiles’ AI alter ego, Technelegy, voiced as zeroes and ones, layered with human- and machine-generated sound – evoking ancient data transmissions in the oral tradition as well as the immersive potential of multisensorial, multimedia, metaversal language and literature. Brought into existence via the blockchain, it is a new form of “token word poetry.”


As with the duo’s other poetry “unreadings,” all minters will receive an airdropped broadside of the full poem after all editions are collected. A 1/1 media-rich version of the entire poem will also be made available. 
 
Poetic traits:
- 321 editions performed by the algorithm, out of billions of possible combinations
- Each unique piece contains between 3 and 6 (out of 60) lines of generative text from a poem by Technelegy – a custom text generator fine-tuned on Stiles’ writing and research material, seeded with prompts from Stiles’ and Stern’s work – translated into binary and performed by Stiles
- 24 possible binary backbeats performed by Stern in his “Nathaniel Fun Time” (NFT) stylings, and generatively re-mixed
- 98 possible intros
- 15 musical stems composed by Kris Bones, generating millions of possible mixes
- Thousands of possible ending combinations 
- 5 fonts, layered in billions of potential ways, including Stern and Stiles’ custom AI font, NNFT (Neural Network Font Type), developed for their ongoing collaboration, “Mother Computer”
- 13 color palettes based on Stern and Stiles’ respective artworka
- Very rare attributes including music-less performance, poem-less music, repeated “B1nary 0de” (title only)

Click to start and stop or replay. Although the first play through will be the same every time, starting and stopping may create minor variations in your mix (though not any of the core attributes).

0RAL B1NARY: “BINARY ODE” was produced with partial support from Refraction DAO’s Creative Grants program, and premiered as part of Refraction Festival at Art Basel Miami 2022. 15% of primary sales go to Refraction, and 5% of primary sales will be donated to Black Girls Code.

metadata.name: [fxhashturnsone] 2022 A Generative Odyssey #125
metadata.description:
🪐🌌✨

2022 A Generative Odyssey (Story of a traveler)

A simple space landscape generator 🏞
Allows some exploration for curious ones 📡
Don't forget to press "4" to take a panoramic picture 📸🤳

🕳🧭🛰



-----
* Technics *

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Pure code / no external assets
- Interactive / orbitable
- 8 scenes with unlimited possible variations
- 5 capture / screenshot modes 8K+

-----
* Controls *

Left click / touch + drag : orbit around center of interest
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

Keyboard "1" : PNG capture the current view at same resolution / ratio 
Keyboard "2" : PNG capture view as square 4320x4320
Keyboard "3" : PNG capture at best resolution 8K (7680x4320)
Keyboard "4" : PNG capture as panoramic view (8192x2304)
Keyboard "5" : PNG capture as super-panoramic (10650x3000)

-----
* URL modifier *

"&r=1"
enables auto rotation of view (equivalent to "R" key press)

-----
* Mint details *

- Mint preview / capture is PNG 1920x1920

-----
@HAL09999 – May/November 2022

metadata.name: In Due Time #178
metadata.description:
“In Due Time” is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht’s mastery of line and Vittoria’s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria’s poem for the collection:

“In Due Time”
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click “open” under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits “1” through “9” to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.
